  "",
  "The impact zone is defined as the eleven tracts whose centroids fall within a half-mile Euclidean distance of the geographic center of the Obama Presidential Center site, which we take as the intersection of Stony Island Avenue and East 62nd Place (41.7806°N, 87.5879°W, verified against the 2020 site plan; Obama Foundation 2020). The half-mile radius is chosen for comparability with Kim (2018), Immergluck and Balan (2018), and the IHS (2023) impact-zone analyses. The tracts are, for the record: 4201, 4202, 4203, 4204, 4205, 4206, 4207, 4301, 4302, 4303, and 4304 in the 2020 Cook County FIPS identifiers.",
