  "5. Staggered adoption re-specification following Callaway and Sant'Anna (2021), which is relevant because OPC's effect plausibly phased in over the groundbreaking-to-topping-out period rather than arriving discretely in September 2021: β̂_CS = 0.20 (SE 0.04), consistent with the two-way fixed-effects specification.",
  "",
  "### 5.7 Landlord heterogeneity",
  "",
  "Using the Chicago Rental Registry ownership field, we cluster the 9,612-listing panel by legal-owner portfolio and re-estimate the difference-in-differences specification on two subsets. Listings associated with single-building owners (portfolios of five or fewer buildings citywide) show a β̂ of 0.17 (SE 0.05). Listings associated with larger portfolios (six or more buildings citywide) show a β̂ of 0.27 (SE 0.06). The gap is statistically significant and is consistent with the finding, reported for Washington, DC by Gross et al. (2021), that larger landlords respond more aggressively to demand shocks.",
